      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos from the james webb telescope and it just hit me... everything we do, every single feeling or struggle, it's all just noise. in a few billion years the sun is gone and eventually the whole universe just goes cold and dark. does any of this actually matter? it feels like we're just playing pretend in a void that doesn't even care we exist.",
